If you donâ€™t get what Iâ€™m saying is the Liam Neeson is recreating Planes, Trains and Auto-mobiles. Overall its a really fun action flick that you donâ€™t need to take seriously but its fun to watch. It stars Liam Neeson, Vera Farmiga, Patrick Wilson, Jonathan Banks, Elizabeth McGovern and Sam Neill. Its about insurance salesman Michael who is on his daily commute home, which quickly becomes anything but routine. After being contacted by a mysterious stranger, Michael is forced to uncover the identity of a hidden passenger on the train before the last stop. As he works against the clock to solve the puzzle, he realizes a deadly plan is unfolding, and he is unwittingly caught up in a criminal conspiracy that carries life and death stakes for everyone on the train. #thecommuter #movie #cinema #moviereview #moviemadness6

è¯„è®ºäººï¼šthemoviehouse02
è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-02-11
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šMy first review! 'The Commuter' was the first movie I saw in 2018, and I'll therefore review it first. The premise of the movie, despite being a concurring premise, is pretty interesting. The plot is pretty good and driven by Michael's (Liam Neeson) love for his family. What I don't like about the story is that the movie ends, and there is still some mystery and unanswered questions. Vera Farmiga's character feels purposeless at the end of the movie and questions surrounding her remain untouched, which leaves her being a weak character. The action is fine for the most part but sometimes the way it's shot feels too extra in such a narrow area which is a train. In fact, the best parts are when Michael investigates subtly, rather than when he engages in action. During his investigations, the main character makes some rather questionable decisions that make you wonder where exactly he's trying to reach. The performances are good, and Liam Neeson stands out as usual. Overall, The Commuter is an enjoyable movie but feels like there's a bit more left to see by the end. Rating: 68% (D+) #movie #movies #film #films #theater #cinema #thecommuter #thecommutermovie #2018 #liamneeson #verafarmiga #themovie #themoviehousereviews

è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-02-08
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šWe watched The Commuter in the #movietheater. There are a lot of people comparing this to Nonstop. I can see why, both are thrillers on forms of transportation starring #LiamNeeson, but #thecommuter has a better script and makes for a more enjoyable #movie. Neeson plays Michael, an ex cop that has been working as an insurance salesman for the last ten years. He rides the commuter train into #NewYork each day, but then he gets laid off. He gets some drinks with his old partner Alex Murphy (not Robocop ğŸ˜‚) played by #PatrickWilson. We also meet the police chief (#SamNeill), who Michael is surprised has risen that far. On his way home, a mysterious woman approaches him (#VeraFarmiga) and offers him $100K to find a person on the train. Heâ€™s desperate for money after losing his job and decides to play along. Little does he know what will happen once he finds the person. He begins to get an idea when he tries to call for help. People are killed and his family is in danger. Itâ€™s a good #thriller with some #mystery elements. The villains are very Machiavellian, but a huge corruption conspiracy is hinted and I like that we are kept mostly in the dark about it. It allows the villains motive to remain unknown. I also like that the #film subverts expectations on certain characters. It was solid and entertaining. â­ï¸â­ï¸â­ï¸â­ï¸

Cerita yang ditawarkan The Commuter relatif sederhana, hampir sama dengan film-film Liam Neeson sebelumnya seperti Taken dan Non-Stop â€” Liam Neeson diminta menyelesaikan sebuah tugas demi menyelamatkan keluarganya. . Meskipun premis cerita yang ditawarkan cenderung membosankan, tapi tidak membuat film ini kehilangan keistimewaannya. Penonton dibuat seolah-olah ikut berada di dalam kereta, merasakan ancaman yang ada. Apa lagi bagi para anker (anak kereta) yang sehari-harinya menggunakan kereta commuter line untuk beraktivitas. . Adegan action di dalam kereta juga cukup membuat jantung terpacu saat menonton film ini. Twist dibagian akhir yang cukup tak tertebak juga membuat film ini sangat patut untuk disaksikan, terutama bagi para penggemar film Liam Neeson sebelumnya. Perasaan kaget, tegang, dan naiknya adrenalin pasti akan dirasakan saat menonton film berdurasi 105 menit ini. Siapa yang belum nonton? Yakin ga penasaran sama film yang satu ini? The Commuter is another paired effort between Liam Neeson and director Jaume Collet-Serra. I really liked their airplane movie â€œNon-Stopâ€, and The Commuter is almost the same plot but on a train and Neesonâ€™s character is more vulnerable. Letâ€™s start with the positives. Liam Neeson is great once again here, chipping in a splendid performance and doing well in the action sequences. He may be getting old, but he can still pack many punches. The action is filmed quite nicely, not a lot of shaky cam and relying more on the emotional weight. You feel the punches and kicks thrown onboard the train. I also liked the sense of less atmosphere on the train, since it is an enclosed location. The camerawork and cinematography are great. Coming to the performances, I felt everyone else did serviceable. Patrick Wilson was fine, Vera Farmiga seemed wasted and a little off-key with her boring character, and Sam Neill was decent as the lead officer. Of course Neeson is worth making this movie enjoyable. The movie knows what it is, a simple thriller with a somewhat convoluted plot sadly. Itâ€™s never fully explained why Liam Nelsonâ€™s character is brought onto this mission. Into the negatives. Thereâ€™s some really bad CGI in the nighttime sequences when the train crashes. The third act suffers with predictability to the villain, and the slow pacing can be felt. Overall, I felt The Commuter was a fine action movie, light on character development and stronger on entertainment value. ________________________ Verdict: â­ï¸â­ï¸â­ï¸ #thecommuter #liamneeson #moviereview #movie #filmreview #film #theconjuring

è¯„è®ºäººï¼šthe_cynic_critic
è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-02-05
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šMy review of â€œThe Commuterâ€- Going into this movie, my expectations werenâ€™t too high. Working at my job for several hours prior, I was psychically and mentally exhausted, and I simply wanted to watch a fun movie that wouldnâ€™t require me to use my brain too hard. With this in mind, â€œThe Commuterâ€ is exactly the kind of movie I wanted it to be, for better and (occasionally) for worse. Featuring frequent collaborators Liam Neeson and director Jaume Collet-Serra, this action flick is about a man named Michael who gets caught up in a criminal conspiracy while on a train after accepting a job that is given to him by a fellow passenger. Michael (played by Liam Neeson) is a pretty normal and unremarkable guy, with the films great opening segment showing just how repetitive (yet still enjoyable) his life his. Unfortunately, his life comes crashing down once he is inexplicably fired from his job, and he heads back home, sad and ashamed, on the train he has been on almost every day for the past ten years. Joanna (played by Vera Farmiga) is aware of Michaelâ€™s familiarity with the train and his recent firing, and uses these facts to give Michael an offer he canâ€™t resist; for 100,000 dollars, he has too simply find someone on the train whom he feels doesn't belong. As Michael accepts the task, the movie kicks into gear. For a significant chunk of the movie, the pacing is swift and snappy, and I was captivated by the chaos that was taking place. Liam Neeson is to be thanked for my captivation, for he helps make Michael a very relatable and sympathetic character, which in turn makes one heavily invested in the fire journey he takes. Thankfully, this journey is well directed by Jaume Collet-Serra, who makes the action sequences very fun to look at and successfully allows the tension to pile onto itself. One fight in particular (involving an ax) had me on the edge of my seat as the fight neared its intense conclusion. Unfortunately, while this particular fight scene has a satisfying conclusion, the same canâ€™t be said for the movie as a whole. (Continued in the comments section)

Yeah Iâ€™ve seen it too and I just rewatched the exact same film only this time itâ€™s on a train and itâ€™s called The Commuter! And hereâ€™s the thing - I enjoyed it...again! Taken was terrible (I didnâ€™t bother watching 2 & 3) but it gave Neeson a new lease of life as an ageing action star and for the most part, his B-movie action films with this director have all been surprisingly enjoyable. This film also includes the best fight on a train since Sean Connery and Robert Shaw in From Russia With Love. One thing thatâ€™s really lacking in todayâ€™s cinematic climate is the mid budget action/thrillers of the 80â€™s and 90â€™s - where are your buddy cop movies? Your psychosexual drama? Your John Grisham adaptations? Your ticking clock suspense movies? Of late this is about as close as weâ€™ve gotten to a straight up, fun B-movie and Iâ€™ll take(n) it. Instantly forgettable but fun all the same. SHE SAID: Imagine playing Cluedo with Agatha Christie on a train and Liam Neeson is your board piece: thatâ€™s The Commuter! The film opens with a sleek montage of mornings, giving depth to Neesonâ€™s cop-turned-insurance broker backstory. His life immediately feels real, and we are ready to believe that he could and would wind up in one hell of an afternoon commute. Neeson is often an oxymoron: strong in stature but soft in manner. Here is a prime example, as he tries to locate a mysterious passenger while being framed as a hijacker who has seen Falling Down one too many times. We believe that he could beat a man using an electric guitar and that he could look like a nice guy while doing it. The Commuter is, to be fair, Non-stop on train tracks. And Iâ€™m ok with that. Next up, I hope Neeson and director Jaume Collet-Serra do a murder mystery on a cruise ship. They could call it Taken on Board!

è¯„è®ºäººï¼šmoviereviews7
è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-02-04
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šThe Commuter ~ PG-13 ~ 2018 ~ #JaumeColletSerra #LiamNeeson #VeraFarmiga #PatrickWilson #JonathanBanks #SamNeill #ColinMcFarlane After being laid off, a financially struggling businessman is offered the opportunity to find a specific person that doesnâ€™t belong on his daily commuter train for a large amount of money. Okay, so I actually enjoyed this movie a lot more than I thought I would. Liam Neeson has had this stereotype ever since Taken where he plays yet another badass old guy in a mediocre, forgettable action movie. While The Commuter might still fall under that category, it definitely exceeded my expectations. Donâ€™t get me wrong, there still are a fair amount of notable flaws. Character development was kept to a minimum, the acting was all relatively poor, & the third act is littered with an absurd amount of illogical writing. Regardless, this movie did what itâ€™s main goal was: to entertain. As little invested as I was in the characters, the story remains consistent & fails to have a dull moment. The movie never takes itself too seriously, so I never really felt like the film was failing to do what it was trying to. I enjoyed the multiple scenarios Neesonâ€™s character put himself in & even when the third act got a little over-the-top, I was still having fun. Would I ever watch this again on my own? Probably not. But I definitely didnâ€™t find it to be the slightest of chores to watch this cheap thriller. 3/5 #TheCommuter #train #passenger #passengertrain #commuter #action #mystery #thriller #movie #film #moviereview

è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šThe Commuter is a movie starring Liam Neeson and directed by Jaume Collet-Sierra. The movie is about a man who is tasked by a woman to find a person with a certain bag going to a certain place and kill them. The movie is solid for the first two acts. Itâ€™s a nice action thriller with a race against the clock twist in an enclosed environment. Itâ€™s a fun movie, but with some odd â€œscrew the upper-classâ€ sentiments thrown in, but still solid. It brings good performances, and surprisingly good, but gimmicky direction. The third act, however goes completely off the rails, pardon my pun. It shifts the movieâ€™s focus away from the interesting half mystery half action movie I was expecting, to a very overblown CGI mess. Without giving anything away, it almost shifts types of action movies to a completely different sub genre, and does some things that make no rational sense and may not even be possible. Another issue I have, is with the dialogue. Itâ€™s all very hokey and unrealistic. The attempts at comedy fall flat and the attempt at relating to the audience fails. All in all, itâ€™s a perfectly passable movie, that is only accentuated by Jaume Collet-Sierraâ€™s direction. #film #moviereview #movie #review #cinema #liamneeson #action #thriller #mystery #actionmovie #thecommuter #train

è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼š[Movie Review] The Commuter (2018) #KataKinema . The Commuter stars Liam Neeson as Michael McCauley, an ex-insurance salesman who is confronted by a mysterious woman, named Joanna (Vera Farmiga), on his daily commute home. Little did he know that Joanna is bad news, now Michael is blackmailed into finding someone on the train, where not only the lives of his family are at stake, but also the lives of everyone on the train. . I like the action scenes, I think they are well shot and well choreographed. I also like the thrilling whodunit moments. What I dislike, however, is the movie is taking itself too seriously, while there a lot of implausibilities and a few plot holes. If it doesnâ€™t take itself seriously, I think I mightâ€™ve ignored the flaws and enjoyed it a little more. In conclusion, this movie is an enjoyable and thrilling action movie, only when you donâ€™t try to make sense out of it. But if you do, it turns into an enjoyable, mindless, silly, and thrilling action movie. . KinemaScore: 2.5 out of 5 . So, what do you guys think? Let us know in the comment section! . Happy watching and weâ€™ll see you at the movies :D . è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šMovies of the Future: Weekend Box-Office Results 1: Maze Runner ($24.1M) 2: Jumanji ($16.1M) 3: Hostiles ($10.1M) 4: Greatest Showman ($9.5M) 5: The Post ($9.1M) Last weekend Maze Runner: The Death Cure was the major new release and it disappointed. However with its overseas numbers, it's already over $100M worldwide, but probably won't beat The Scorch Trials total of $312M worldwide. Jumanji just cant slow down with an amazing 17% drop as it'll soon race past $850M worldwide. Hostiles had a decent theatre expansion with a $10M haul. The Greatest Showman continues to boast incredible holds, but it'll just fall short of $300M worldwide. The Post is also doing god business, compared to 12 strong and Den of Thieves which has significantly slowed down. The Shape Of Water expanded further and got some good results but $50M worldwide isn't that great.

è¯„è®ºäººï¼šcineviewid
è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-02-02
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šTHE COMMUTER CINERATE: 7 out of 10 CINEOPSYS Michael menghabiskan hari-harinya hidupnya di kereta utk perjalanan dr rmh ke tempat kerja. Hingga suatu hari, kedekatan hidupnya dengan dunia kereta sangat diperlukan utk memecahkan misteri yang membuat Michael, secara tidak langsung, terjebak dalam sebuah konspirasi kejahatan. CINENOTES Film ini sangat menonjolkan Liam Neeson sebagai tokoh protagonis. Sempitnya ruang geral di dalam kereta membuat semua aksi Liam Neeson terlihat maksimal. Untungnya, Liam memberikan performa terbaiknya untuk film ini. Awal film ini sangat artistik, sinematografi yang memukau terasa kira-kira sampai 20-25 menit pertama, selebihnya tidak ada efek visual yang sedinamis awalnya. Film ini memiliki logika filmnya sendiri, terutama bila mau mengupas logiks konspirasinya, sehingga cukup ditonton dengan menikmati setiap adegannya. Ada banyak kritik di dalamnya bila mau berpikir lebih keras, tapi sebuah pesan yang normatif. Kesimpulannya, film ini adalah sebuah cerita yang sederhana, dikemas dengan konspirasi yang pelik. (JD / @cineviewID) #moviereview #ulasanfilm #filmreview #movies #film #reviewfilm #cinema #sinema #cinephile #instamovies #instamovie #instafilm #instareview #thecommuter #hollywood #liamneeson

è¯„è®ºäººï¼šthe_honest_usher
è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-01-31
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šThe Commuter Directed by: Jaume Collet-Serra Starring: Liam Neeson, Patrick Wilson, Vera Farmiga A man on his daily commute back home is approached by a stranger with a hypothetical preposition, and a reward that is not so hypothetical. The first thing of notice that makes this a clever and engaging ride is the editing and camerawork; films primarily set in one location can easily become repetitive and lack the ability to make the audience anticipate what will happen next. Here however the editing creates a quickened pace that moves the plot along and makes this film feel like its supposed to (a thriller). It also manages to convey visual story-telling in a way that is so effective it removes the need for exposition. The camerawork keeps the location from ever feeling too familiar, the varying use of close-ups and tracking wide shots are relevant to the mood of the protagonist; and this causes his motivations and inner conflicts to be easily displayed on-screen. Not that that would be an issue anyway, as Liam Neeson proves again that he is the best at playing an "everyday-man" who knows how to kick ass. The film has a strong cast, although most of the other actors and actresses feel like they are only in cameo roles next to Neeson, who to allow the narrative to work well, is mostly isolated for the majority of the film. The tension is well built and it comes from being able to easily draw empathy from Neeson's performance; that is his best since Taken. The narrative proceeds logically although it bares a lot of noticeable similarities to other films (many of which I can't mention because...spoilers) but despite this it manages to be better than the films it either draws inspiration from or is coincidentally parallel to. The only negative to be seen is the fact that Neeson's character appears to have John McClane syndrome, and can be put through a lot more physical trauma than what you would expect of a man of his age, it doesn't detract from the fun of watching Neeson in action again but it is rather prevalent, and does have an impact on the validity of the character. Overall, a fast and cleverly put-together train ride that gives plenty to think about. 9/10

è¯„è®ºäººï¼šframereel
è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-01-31
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šNext on the Liam Neeson's Transportation Conspiracy! THE COMMUTER Commuting isn't the most fertile source for interest when it comes to a movie, it's about a boring routine that you passionlessly do to get from point A to B. This film emulates all the thrills of commuting and resolves to meld them to an unnecessarily complicated plot. And, you know, it can be nice to take the train for the first time but once you've done it several times, it stops being refreshing. As so, if you see the same movie played out with slight differences over the course of a year, you lack that feeling of renewal - that's why John Wick's film are so appreciated, they bring something new. After having seen Non Stop and Run All Night, you can't help to be indifferent to the same actor-director combination, specially when the cuts, characters and plot feel the same, Jaume Collet-Serra's storyboard decisions feel the same and even the colour grading seems to gloom across all this transportation method trilogy. However, although it's completely uneventful, I didn't dislike The Commuter. There's a security in a commute like this where the elements are so played out that they are bound to work. Furthermore, there is one shot that is incredibly good and there is actual tension built around a premise, which many action films fail to do. It's like going to work in an office, it's a service and in this case, enough has been done to make it serviceable. It's incoherent but it has a lot of personal style, it's cookie-cutter but it is sufficiently well put together to make you actually care and feel some suspense for what's going to happen next. It's no Unstoppable or (for Hitchcock's sake) Strangers on a Train, but its main strength comes from the realization that the movie consists on seemingly one-trick pony of a star kicking ass in yet another mode of transport. #thecommuter #liamneeson #verafarmiga #filmreview #filmcritic

è¯„è®ºäººï¼šobfilmreviews
è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-01-30
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šHere's a list of all the new releases that I watched this month with my ratings. 1) Three billboards outside ebbing, Missouri - 9/10 I heard a lot of great things about this but I wasn't expecting to love it as much as I did. This was the first film I watched in 2018, and I expect it to be in my top 5 come the end of the year. Frances Mcdormand and Sam Rockwell were brilliant and I expect them both to win Oscars. ----------------------------- 2) Molly's game - 8/10 I didn't know anything about Molly Bloom going into this, and I think that made me enjoy the movie more because I didn't know how things ended up for her. Jessica Chastain was brilliant and really owned the movie - there isn't anyone who would have been better cast. ----------------------------- 3)Coco - 8/10 It's definitely up there with being one of the better Disney films. I didn't know a lot about the Day of the Dead but having seen this I feel like it's given me a whole new outlook on death - I thought the movie did a great job showing off the culture and tradition. ----------------------------- 4)The Commuter - 7/10 Liam Neeson on public transport fighting to keep his family alive. You knew exactly what you're going to get and it didn't disappoint. ----------------------------- 5) The Post - 7/10 I thought it was well made and had great performances from Meryl Streep and Tom Hanks. However I found the actual story to be quite boring in parts ----------------------------- 6) 12 Strong - 7/10 Although the actual true story is unbelievable, I thought the film fell short of capturing this. However I thought the action scenes were great and it had some good performances, showing that they were just normal men that were sent to fight. ----------------------------- 7) Hostiles 6/10 Again another one with decent performances, and when there was action it was quite intense. However when there wasn't any action it felt quite dull and dragged on a bit longer than it needed to be ----------------------------- 8) Early Man - 3/10 I knew this would be shit and it didn't fail at that, was full of stupid accents that were there to make little kids laugh. I'm not even sure if I like football anymore

è¯„è®ºäººï¼ša_movie_critic
è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-01-28
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼š"The Commuter" was another thriller by Liam Neeson and it does not disappoint in the cinema, but when you're done with the movie, you kind of reflect back on the things that didn't make sense but did while you were watching it. First: thing: The Plot. I was very intrigued with the storyline but it did turn out a little bit unrealistic at the end. The mystery to the movie was acceptable but some parts were predictable and the person who did not belong on the train was not expected. Second: the cast and characters. Liam Neeson was pretty good in his role and Vera Farmiga was ok, so was Patrick Wilson. I did like how Jonathan Banks was in it because he was amazing in "Breaking Bad". Everyone else was average. Finally: the music and editing. The action scenes were not well done and the original score for the movie did not blend well with the whole suspense and plot. The editing is not really something to appreciate because (SPOILER) there is a scene where the train is moving sideways for a long amount of time and that is impossible. This movie wasn't a big success in reviews it it is a fan favorite now which is why I am going to rate this movie with a 62%. Thank you guys for reading my review and I'll see you next time. Bye! #the #commuter #thecommuter #liamneeson #verafarmiga #patrickwilson #jonathanbanks #mystery #thriller #action #movie #movienight #moviereview #review #moviecritic #critic #university #nyu #chapman #syracuse #loyola #lafi #amoviecritic

è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šMOVIE REVIEW: If you're willing to turn your brain off and enjoy yourself, #TheCommuter is a surprisingly good time. There is a lot more tension and excitement than we anticipated. Much of the action enters into over the top, "what the hell is physics?" territory, but let's face it, we don't seek out #LiamNeeson action films for their realism. The mystery has a little bit of intrigue, though it is not tightly put together and we never felt wowed by that aspect of it. The camerawork gets pretty shaky at times and the jump-cuts come a bit too often, especially in the beginning when. #VeraFarmiga, #PatrickWilson, #FlorencePugh, #JonathanVanks, #ElizabethMcGovern, and #SamNeill don't get anything to do, but Neeson still keeps the entire thing rolling with help from director #JaumeColletSerra. Our rating: 6.5/10! #moviereview #lololovesfilms #cinephile #cinephilecommunity See the FULL REVIEW by clicking the link in our @lololovesfilms bio/profile above, or visit us on the blog here: http://bit.ly/LoloCOMMUTER

è¯„è®ºäººï¼šmovies_of_the_future
è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-01-25
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šMovies of the Future: Weekend Box-Office Results 1: Jumanji ($19.5M) 2: 12 Strong ($15.8M) 3: Den of Thieves ($15.2M) 4: The Post ($11.7M) 5: Greatest Showman ($10.6M) The past, weekend Jumanji reigned supreme for the fourth weekend in a row beating out the two newcomers. Jumanji is racing towards $800M worldwide, as has already become Sony's highest grossing (non Spiderman) movie in America. 12 Strong beat Den Of Thieves but both performed miserably as stars Chris Hemsworth and Gerard Butler prove they can't match box-office results from their bigger franchises (Thor and Has Fallen, respectively). The Post had an impressive hold as it passes $50M worldwide, but not a good as hold as The Greatest Showman with 14%, crossing $200M worldwide. Paddington 2 also had a strong hold of under 30% but is lacking behind its predecessor sadly. Proud Mary suffered a huge 60% drop, as all the awards movies has decent holds.

è¯„è®ºäººï¼šjimbobtalksmovies
è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-01-25
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šThe Commuter (2018) Movie Review #thecommuter #moviereview #jimbobtalksmovies. SPOILERS (You have been warned). This is the first movie of 2018 I'm reviewing, The Commuter is a mixture of Non-Stop, Taken and Speed all in one if you ask me, is that a bad thing? No it's not but it is something we've all seen before. The Commuter stars Liam Neeson as Michael, an ex cop, husband and father who commutes on a train every day for work until one day he loses his job. On the train he is confronted by a strange woman who asks him to find a person on the train who does not belong and in return he gets $100,000. This movie is a race against the clock as Neeson puts all his best efforts and skills he learnt as a cop to try and find the mysterious character known as Prin who is aboard the train before his family is killed. The Commuter has great action sequences, it has 2 very good fight scenes that don't rely on great stunt work but make it work. Neeson once again is brilliant as the action hero but there are a few plot holes in this movie and it's nothing we haven't seen before, The Commuter is very much like Non-Stop but on a train. Overall there is great acting in this movie and great action scenes but brings nothing new to the table, The Commuter gets #7.5/10 from @JimbobTalksMovies. #thecommuterjimbobtalksmovies #actionfilmreviewsjimbobtalksmovies.

è¯„è®ºäººï¼špeterwilsonreviews
è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-01-25
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šThe Commuter: This time he's on a train and it's nearly just as much fun as the "non-stop" plane. Also the Warren's from the conjuring take a break from ghosts and dabble in action but add a nice charm to the character of the film. Liam Neeson is what you come to expect in these style of films but there's nothing wrong with that, it's his niche!! I'm glad they kept the character the same age as Neeson himself, he shows at 60 you can still throw quite a few punches and he always has that commanding presence which adds to the tone of his likeable characters. I personally found the 2nd half better than the first. It felt quite comparable to the film Speed (not as good) towards the end. Especially with the intensity of the music and slightly comparable situation. Overall its alot of fun, you go to see these sort of films for the entertaining action and the thrill of the main characters journey and challenges. I was looking forward to this film as I've always enjoyed films with trains, I don't know why but I always find that setting intense and thrilling and enjoyable to watch. I look forward to the iTunes HD release! I look forward to more of these films!! è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šThe Commuter (2018) dir. Jaume Collet-Serra - 3/5 - FILM REVIEW - Final Part The direction by Jaume Collet-Serra is grounded as well it can be on a train-location and is appropriately silly when it needs to be when the film shows its flair for action. I did like the opening montage however, that shows the day-to-day life of It's a film that's fully aware of what a Liam Neeson action film is, overdoses a little bit with the concept, gives Neeson plenty of arse to kick and he kicks it bloody well in one one-take fight sequence. So I suppose this film might deserve a 2/5 rating, right? Well it goes back to point I made at the start of this: there's a time and a place for a Liam Neeson action flick. It's self-aware, has an interesting if flawed concept that falls flat eventually and knows what it wants to do as a straight-up action film. The kind of mindless action film that used to get produced and released a lot in the 80's and 90's. It's the kind of film that you might think would be worth it on home-release, but in all honesty, if you don't take the film too seriously, it might just be worth the Â£5 film ticket - but perhaps not more. It does it's job in being a very flawed entertaining Liam Neeson action vehicle. #thecommuter #thecommuterfilm #jaumecolletserra #2018 #liamneeson #verafarmiga #patrickwilson #jonathanbanks #elizabethmcgovern #samneill #film #filmreview #instamovies #instafilm #action #thriller

è¯„è®ºäººï¼šliquid.reviews

è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šThe Commuter (2018) dir. Jaume Collet-Serra - 3/5 - FILM REVIEW - Part 3 The cast do a lot with very little, or at least a very thin script and for the most part they're all capable. It just seems that some of the actors are capable of much more and deserve more when it comes to a better and competent script, rather than just being functional entities to the plot. The plot itself seems to forget the setup half-way through and the film then returns to familiar ground: Liam Neeson beating the shit out of bad guys, or rather other commuters. I dunno, maybe it's something we can sympathise with and want to do when on our commutes with fellow commuters of the annoying variety. I did hate the sort of "Unstoppable" moment that the film took with the train concept towards the end of the film and it was just pointless and a drastic shift in the film's already troubled pacing. #thecommuter #thecommuterfilm #jaumecolletserra #2018 #liamneeson #verafarmiga #patrickwilson #jonathanbanks #elizabethmcgovern #samneill #film #filmreview #instamovies #instafilm #action #thriller

è¯„è®ºäººï¼šliquid.reviews
è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-01-25
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šThe Commuter (2018) dir. Jaume Collet-Serra - 3/5 - FILM REVIEW - Part 2 Admittedly, I haven't actually seen Taken in full, nor have I seen any of the action movies that he has starred in recent years; I've just never really had a chance to get into them and watch them properly for some reason. I think it's important to remember that there's a special place reserved in cinemas for the straight-forward, hard and tough-as-nails action/crime/thriller genre movies akin to those of 70s Hollywood films. The sort of films that you could just sit back, watch, take it in and just enjoy. Neeson has managed to do something really special over the last decades with his career in this respect, being involved in the sort of films that you can watch and be entertained by very easily. The beauty of The Commuter is in it's Hitchcock-like simplicity in terms of the plot (at first). This gradually deteriorates however and less favourable when it overdoses on the action part way through. An ex-cop turned normal insurance salesman (those cop "skills" will come in handy no doubt...wink-wink) on a train, put in the right place at the right time, by the wrong people for the wrong reasons, forced to do some bad things. A labyrinthine game of Saw-like proportions begins; it's a race against time, a race against Neeson's own paranoia, where everyone on board the train is his target. It's the simple and one-location game that takes place and the films thriller moments that makes this entertaining. #thecommuter #thecommuterfilm #jaumecolletserra #2018 #liamneeson #verafarmiga #patrickwilson #jonathanbanks #elizabethmcgovern #samneill #film #filmreview #instamovies #instafilm #action #thriller

è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šThe Commuter (2018) dir. Jaume Collet-Serra - 3/5 - FILM REVIEW - Part 1 There's a time and place for a Liam Neeson action flick. Sometimes something is taken. I've often heard Neeson has a particular set of skills, skills that make him a nightmare for the bad bastards who get in his way; and if he doesn't get what he wants, he looks for said bad bastards, find them, beats them up and kills them. Maybe he does this in different countries, maybe he does this whilst taking a taxi or plane trip or against wolves in the wild. Essentially, we know Liam Neeson beating the shit out of bad guys, on the big-screen is worth a watch, even if the story heavily falters. So with that in mind, how does The Commuter fair? Pretty well if you're looking if you're not looking for much in consistency and just want to sit back for a silly watch. Since Neeson's career took a major turning point in 2008 with the release of Taken, he redefined his career and has been in the action film business since and shows no signs of stopping any time soon. As well as being a formidable actor with tremendous gravitas (see Schindler's List, Gangs of New York, Batman Begins, Kingdom of Heaven) he lends himself to the action movie genre very well, delivering capable performances whilst delivering on the action-front from a physical perspective, putting effort into the fighting and action sequences. #thecommuter #thecommuterfilm #jaumecolletserra #2018 #liamneeson #verafarmiga #patrickwilson #jonathanbanks #elizabethmcgovern #samneill #film #filmreview #instamovies #instafilm #action #thriller

è¯„è®ºäººï¼šmichaldraker
è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-01-24
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼š#TheCommuter was my first official movie of 2018 ... and shit ... it couldn't start worse. I like Collet-Serra and his movies. I like Neeson and his action roles. This was to me unnecessary filled with action. It was to the point of stupidity and absurdity. I liked the set up for the movie, but after first stop (second?) when certain character dies, it just goes to hell and never came back. What could have been suspensful movie, (which Collet-Serra can do), was just washed out, boring and annoying movie. Action sequences were good, I'll give them that, but they didn't fit it. Movie tried to be smart, I'll give them that, but it didn't work. It was predictable, uneventful, also long, with bad characters I didn't care about for a split second. Avoid this movie in cinemas, rent it if you so desire later this year. 1/5* P.S. First movie since #WonderWoman when I stormed out of cinema right when credits were about to roll ... and the final scene ... oh lord ... I could rant for so long ... aaaaaaah. P.S.S. At the opening credits there was really funny bit - to me at least - Sam Neil's named showed up, and I went "Whaaaat ..." split second later Neeson's character said "What" in the movie. I thought it was maybe directors decission to acknowladge fact Sam Neill is in this movie and it might surprise some people me included - I'm probably reading to much into it. #Movies

è¯„è®ºäººï¼šfantastic.mr.movies
è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-01-24
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šThe Commuter- 7/10 â€¢A common businessman is caught in the middle of a conspiracy on the way homeâ€¢ The Commuter impressed me in a lot of ways I didnâ€™t expect it to. For an action movie I found it surprising that most scenes were dialogue driven and the film was very heavy on plot. While itâ€™s always exciting to watch people beat the crap out of each other for two hours straight, I found this gave the film lots of depth, allowing the full investment and attention of the audience, and causing an action scene (when it does occur) to have all the more impact and intensity. Another thing that is always important is that cause is given to the main character and in the Commuter I feel like relationships were very established. If they werenâ€™t you wouldnâ€™t care who died or why, or even about the main character at all. On top of that, the logic for this movie was rock solid. If I was ever questioning the reasoning of the main character, the problem would immediately be explained or resolved. My problem with this movie is unfortunately a big one. While the hand to hand fight scenes were fantastic to watch, often taking you right into them, the de-railing of the train was extremely dragged out and felt absolutely unnecessary. Considering this was supposed to be the climax of the movie it left me dissatisfied and wishing they wouldâ€™ve taken it a different route. Other than that I really enjoyed The Commuter and thought it was an exciting movie that offers more than youâ€™d expect it to. #movies #thecommuter #commuter #liamneeson #moviereviews #fantasticmrmovies

è¯„è®ºäººï¼šcinema.bioskop

è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼š"THE COMMUTER." (Still Showing on Bioskop ğŸ¬ğŸ‡²ğŸ‡¨) . Cerita yang ditawarkan The Commuter relatif sederhana, hampir sama dengan film-film Liam Neeson sebelumnya seperti Taken dan Non-Stop â€” Liam Neeson diminta menyelesaikan sebuah tugas demi menyelamatkan keluarganya. . Meskipun premis cerita yang ditawarkan cenderung membosankan, tapi tidak membuat film ini kehilangan keistimewaannya. Penonton dibuat seolah-olah ikut berada di dalam kereta, merasakan ancaman yang ada. Apa lagi bagi para anker (anak kereta) yang sehari-harinya menggunakan kereta commuter line untuk beraktivitas. . Adegan action di dalam kereta juga cukup membuat jantung terpacu saat menonton film ini. Twist dibagian akhir yang cukup tak tertebak juga membuat film ini sangat patut untuk disaksikan, terutama bagi para penggemar film Liam Neeson sebelumnya. Perasaan kaget, tegang, dan naiknya adrenalin pasti akan dirasakan saat menonton film berdurasi 105 menit ini. . . Siapa yang belum nonton? Yakin ga penasaran sama film yang satu ini? Like dan tag juga ke teman nonton kalian! . . #thecommuter #cinemabioskop #nowshowing

è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šJoanna: Letâ€™s do an experiment. What if I asked you to do something that could profoundly affect an individual on this train? Michael McCauley: I donâ€™t understand. Joanna: Itâ€™s just one little thing. Someone on this train does not belong, all you have to do is find them. Liam Neeson stars as Michael MacCauley a businessman who is caught up in a criminal conspiracy during his daily commute home. If you think this is just another Liam Neeson movie with Liam Neeson being Liam Neeson and doing Liam Neeson type things...you would be correct! Letâ€™s be honest at this point your not going to see a movie starring Liam Neeson and expect an intricate storyline or world class cinematography. But what you can always expect is a fun ride. The Commuter delivers on that promise with just that, plenty of action and a few good twist every now and then. Pros: Hitchcock: What makes this film fun is that it really seems to draw on an Alfred Hitchcock vibe of whodunnit? Vera Farmiga: best known for her roles as Norma Bates in Bates Motel & The Departed. Farmiga always delivers a convincingly good role. In this case, as a great antagonist Cons: I mean to really pick at this film -Expected corny Lines -While some of the twist were good. è¯„è®ºäººï¼šthefilmguyy
è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-01-23
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šThe Commuter. Seen this twice now, both in IMAX! Films like these rarely get made anymore, but when they do they sure do pack a lot of suspense, thrills and old school action that really make for a captivating fun ride! Directed by Juame Collet-Serra and starring Liam Neeson The Commuter marks their fourth collaboration together (Uknown, Non-Stop, Run All Night and now this) and the two deliver yet another thrilling, edge of your seat action film that does well in mixing mystery and action into one! Serra is one of the best directors in the industry, and does not get the credit he deserves! Neeson, once again, kicks serous ass and proves why he is one of the best action hero's of our time! This film was entertaining and had only a small budget of 30 million dollars, which is quite low compared to a majority of action films made these days! Serra and Neeson should definitely reteam for a fifth film together! And next up for Neeson, Hard Powder, which will be more Neeson killing bad guys and being badass! #TheCommuter #Film #Action #Thriller #JuameColletSerra #LiamNeeson #Badass #Filmmaking #Director #Actor

è¯„è®ºäººï¼šgigi.gendut
è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-01-22
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼š"The Commuter" Director : Jaume Collet-Serra Cast : Liam Neeson, Vera Farmiga, Patrick Wilson, Jonathan Banks,... Pelem yang berkesan bagi pengguna commuter, tapi commuter nya beda dengan di Indonesia walaupun sama2 penuh dan ramai.. Nonton "The Commuter" ini lengkap dapat action dan dramanya. Dan suaranya om Liam yang Optimus Prime nya transformer itu nambah keseruan dari film ini.. Diawali dengan adegan keluarga di Amerika, suami istri bekerja untuk melunasi hutang. Walaupun sudah bekerja sampai usia 60thn tetap saja dipecat. Michael (Liam Neeson) yg mantan polisi, dipecat dari perusahaan asuransi tempat ia bekerja selama 10thn, kemudian masuk perangkap seorang wanita bernama Joana (Vera Farmiga), sosok misterius yg muncul di commuter yg biasa ditumpanginya.. Alur cerita cukup seru, ga ketebak dan menegangkan... Rekomen bgt untuk ditonton bareng pacar atau pasangan, tapi karena banyak adegan kekerasan jangan bawa anak2 dibawah umur ya.. *sumber gambar : internet . . #nonton #bioskopxxi #liamneeson #action #drama #thecommuter #movielover #movieteller #instamovies #hollywood #bioskopindonesia #moviemania #moviereviewer #antispoiler #spoileralert

è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šThe Commuter Time to kick my 2018 movies off with a Liam Neeson action movie. Iâ€™ll be honest with you, this movie doesnâ€™t look good. It looks like another cheesy action flick, but Liam Neeson is the reason Iâ€™m seeing this movie. The guy has had his fair share of bad movies, but this is from the same guy who did Non-Stop. Non-Stop looked like a cheesy action movie, but it actually turned out to be good, I enjoyed most of it. Iâ€™m willing to give this movie a chance. I do find some cheesy action movies more enjoyable then the average movie goer cause I like action. Action movies are an easy to do but hard to pull off form of entertainment. Iâ€™m not expecting much from this movie, Iâ€™m just expecting to be entertained. So with that in mind letâ€™s see what we have in store for us. A businessman is caught up in a criminal conspiracy during his daily commute home. I definitely got what the director was trying to do here, I just think he tried to do too much. This movie starts off simple enough, then once the main plot starts things get really out of hand. I was asking more questions then this movie was answering. Pretty much this movie sets up a bunch of rules for the main character to follow, if he doesnâ€™t follow these rules his family dies, but the main character breaks a bunch of these rules in the second act and nothing happens. There were so many plot holes with this movie that I lost enjoyment by the third act. Also the more this movie goes on, the more insane this movie gets. I was able to find some enjoyment in the middle when the mystery aspect was still in play. So I can give this movie some credit for the second act, but thatâ€™s not much considering how confusing this movie can be. The Commuter tries to recapture the mystery aspect of Non-Stop, but the more information this movie adds to the plot the more confusing it is. Much like any other Liam Neeson action movie, he carries the whole movie. He plays Michael MacCauley whoâ€™s an ex cop who is taking the train home one day and he must find a suspect a woman is looking for or else people die. Itâ€™s easy to have sympathy for this character and he is likable and noble. Continued in Comments.

è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šTHE COMMUTER â€“ 2018 STARS: 6/10 While I think it is fair to say that this is a film in which the action sequences and CGI actually serve the storyline rather than rule it, too much prevenance is still given to eye-candy visuals, resulting in an undeniably entertaining but both implausible and overdone ride on something as basic as a commuter train. The piece is exceptionally well edited and filmed though â€“ or perhaps creatively is the more appropriate word, for the visuals are neither sweeping nor seamless, merely intriguing. Indeed the entire piece reeks of that same intrigue; that fascinating yet decidedly staged vibe that grabs you and draws you in, despite everything your heart and mind tells you. Yes, perhaps you can never be fully engrossed in a story that is so obviously fabricated, but you can certainly be entertained â€“ and that is this film's main plus as far as I am concerned; the ability to hold an audience on an unemotionally connected level. Not unlike one of those cheap but addictive cops and robbers style shows one might see in the evening on television, "The Commuter" somehow manages â€“ with, literally, a hundred suspects, a hundred questions and a virtual time bomb ticking away throughout â€“ to be drawn out, predictable and ultimately unimpressive . . . yet still watchable; still something you would sit down to and not move on from. There is some part of all of us â€“ perhaps â€“ that relishes hours upon hours of unabashed improbability and even as you pretend disinterest in this piece I warrant you will find yourself coming back to that one fateful catch question: what would you do?

è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šWritten by Carlos Crestwell Movie #3 The Commuter. At this point what can you say. Liam Neeson has never been short on work but sense Taken released in 2008 he has been in a steady stream of these well written suspense protagonist vs X dangerous antagonist. He does them very well and as much as youâ€™d like to say enough. Neeson is always so compelling to to sit down and watch that you canâ€™t help but check out his films. This role is no different as he pairs up again with director Jaume Collet-Serra who heâ€™s been around the block with a few times (Non-Stop, Run All Night, Unknown). In this role he plays former NYPD detective turned insurance salesmen Michael MacCauley. A family man with a repetitively boring existence working a 9-5 to support his family. He gets put into a dangerous situation by a mysterious stranger on his usual train route home and Liam Neeson starts to do his thing. Co-stars Vera Farmiga and Patrick Wilson help make up the small bit of star power in this film but itâ€™s well executed seeing how most these films never lose sight of Neeson as their focus. Still another well executed suspense film with very few complaints. These films rarely get too deep in the weeds which is probably a good thing. #Thecommuter #Copperwiire #Loscinema2018

è¯„è®ºäººï¼šfilmgradreview
è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-01-22
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šThe Commuter For god sake Liam, keep your family with you at all times! Now the story of this film is a little bazaar, but it keeps you gripped even if it is set on one of the worst forms of public transport. The film follows Michael MacCauley (Liam Neeson) on his daily commute to his job as an insurance salesman. He has had this job for 10 years and sadly gets let go. On his train ride home that day, a women named Joanna joins Michael in the seat opposite. She posses a hypothetical question where he has to do one thing and in return can earn $100,000. This hypothetical turns out to be real when Michael must find a passenger on the train who doesn't belong who goes by the allias of "Prynne" before Cold springs station or there will be consequences. He just has to find "Prynne" to get the $100,000, but as time runs out and his family become endangered, Michael must figure out who he can and can't trust. Check the Trailer here Now being a big Liam Neeson fan i enjoyed this film. To me all his films are the same, the plot is changed up a bit but most of the films feel formulaic and i found myself thinking alot about Taken. This film although different has alot of action and Neesons character has the lives his family at stake again. For God sake Liam, keep your family with you at all time! That being sad although the movie feels similar to his others, it is still enjoyable and keeps you engaged as you try to work out who "Prynne" is . No spoilers but I totally knew who "Prynne" was. The movie is decent enough, plus Liam Neeson running through the train causing havoc, who doesn't wanna see that. My Film Rating 5/10 ğŸ¥ğŸ¿ #film #filmreview #filmgradreview #movie #cinema #thecommuter #liamneeson #action #thriller #review #train

è¯„è®ºäººï¼šjackoransom97
è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-01-22
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šAn entertaining (and in some places very good) thriller movie. Basic overview without spoiling, is that on his commute back from work Liam Neeson's character is approached by a mysterious woman (Vera Farmiga) who offers him $100,000 to find someone on the train who doesn't belong there and it escalates from there. All the cast are great Neeson is as good as the character type as usual, Patrick Wilson & Vera Farmiga are good supports. Also one thing I didn't expect was too actually find the train passengers as interesting, likeable and well written as they were. The film has some excellent writing and tense directing most so in the dialogue and scenes where he's starting awkward conversations to try and work out who's who and when he's is pacing up and down train trying to work out the situation. The film excels in these areas as they are more thrilling than the action sequences, one of which is awesome (Neeson fighting a dude with a guitar) and delivering an epic one liner after, however the other main fight sequences are just average and you've seen them loads of times before. Speaking of seen before this film doesn't bring much new to the table, if you've seen 'Non-Stop' or other Neeson movies you've basically watched this (not that's that's a bad thing). The ending is fairly predictable and the third act slows down a bit and makes the pacing a bit off and there's some dodgy CGI in places. Overall this a entertaining movie that does what it sets out to do and it's worth a watch for sure ğŸ‘ğŸ»#thecommuter#2018#liamneeson#verafarmiga#patrickwilson#jaumecolletserra#movie#film#cinema

è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼š(1/4) I haven't been able to post anything recently on Instagram because once again I have a lot on my mind with what I'm going through as usual. So, I'm posting right now. On Saturday, January 13th, 2018, I was about to go to Bethany, Connecticut to attend the #OverTheTop event that #NortheastWresrling is having. Then I found out on Twitter that the event was sold out. So, I'm not gonna waste my Saturday away by staying at home watching TV. Therefore, while Northeast Wrestling is having their sold out event, I went to the #RegalCinemas at the #BrassMillCenter and watched #TheCommuter. That movie was really good. #LiamNesson played an ex-cop turned insurance salesman who gets on a train after he found out that his employer is laying him off after working for them for years. Then came a mysterious woman named Sophia played by Vera Farmiga And she tells him that there's money hidden in this train and all he has to do once after he founds the money, is to find a person who does not belong in that train. A person by the name of "Prinn". Then the movie went on like a full-on roller coaster ride, as Liam Nesson is trying to find Prinn before the train reaches Cold Springs. He's questioning people on the train on what's their business. Basically, Sophia has him under her control by threatening Liam's character's family by the phone. Is like Taken and Nonstop but on a train. Then, Liam had to fight a black guitarist turned hired assassin by Sophia on the train and Liam won by throwing him out of the train. In the end, turns out that Prinn is a woman who witnessed the death of a public official by corrupt cops which one of the cops was the former partner of Liam's character and she took a piece of evidence after witnessing it that has something to do with Sophia and now she's on that train going to Cold Springs to meet up with FBI officials and put under protection. There's was a small fight between Liam's character and the former partner and the police killed the former partner by accident with a sniper and everyone in that train is fine and that's after the train got derailed and cops came & surrounded the remaining car. è¯„è®ºäººï¼šmoviemaniac.id
è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-01-22
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šThe Commuter (2018) Movie Maniac rating: 3.5/5 It's the fourth collaboration between Liam Neeson and director Jaume Collet-Serra, and it's also the 7th time Liam Neeson played a tough guy character ever since he starred in Taken. The Commuter feels like a combination of 2011's Source Code (for the train setting) and 2014's Non-Stop (for the mystery killer on board of a moving transportation, and Liam Neeson presence). But despite the average reviews by fellow critics, I really enjoy this movie and this movie is better than Unknown, Non-Stop, and Run All Night. I personally like the editing of the beginning of the movie, the fast forward scenes are unique. The story, well there is no such thing in real world, is unbelievable but it works right on this movie, the villain resembles the villain in 2008's Eagle Eye in which the villain has an eye and ear anywhere and can do anything that sounds impossible. Liam Neeson plays the character very well, mostly like his previous good family man and highly skilled tough guy character. The action scenes are good, some of it are thrilling in fact. The movie really entertains and keeps you guessing until the climax of the movie. Another thing to add, I personally like the drama side of this movie where Liam Nesson's character got laid off from work and he has a burden to finance his kid's tuition. It is realistic and depicts the harsh thing in our lives. In my opinion, if you like Liam Neeson and his previous action movies, then you must see this movie. Don't expect a realistic storyline, just enjoy the movie and have a good time. #thecommuter #liamneeson #movies #film #hollywood #review #hobby #action #2018 @thecommuterfilm @lionsgate @cinema.21 @cinemaxxtheater @cgv.id @cinemagsnews

è¯„è®ºäººï¼šindomoviereview
è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-01-21
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šThe Commuter is a 2018 action thriller film directed by Jaume Collet-Serra. The film follows a man who is unwittingly recruited into a murder conspiracy after meeting a mysterious woman while on his daily train commute. Pros: I go in with zero knowledge of what this film is about and a very low expectation (since you know, itâ€™s a January movie). To my surprise, this is a very solid and entertaining movie with a rather unique premise. It leans heavily towards the mystery-thriller aspect, which is a truly refreshing idea to make the movie stand out (at least for the first half of the runtime). It raises some interesting questions about the morality of the main character, and in a way also allows the character develop in a more entertaining fashion. Liam Neesonâ€™s performance is fantastic and he has a very impressive fight scene around the second act of the film. Cons: Iâ€™d like to call the main issue with this film â€œthe escalation problemâ€. The film does some very questionable and inconsistent decisions throughout the story just in order to escalate the stakes higher and higher every time. At some point it turns from an engaging crime thriller with detective works into an over-the-top full blown action film for no apparent reason other than trying to make the film seemingly have a bigger stakes. There are a lot of plotholes made during this process and honestly Iâ€™d rate this with a much higher score had it simply been a contained thriller inside a train. Verdict: The Commuter is a very pleasant surprise for January movies. Itâ€™s an engaging thriller film with interesting premise, although at some point the film tries to bite more than it can chew. Rating: 3.5/5 #movie #movies #film #review #cinema #moviebuff #moviereview #moviereviews #moviefan #movielover #moviestagram #moviecritic #filmbuff #filmreview #reviewfilm #instafilm #instamovie #instamovies #cinephile #cinephilecommunity #greatmovie #action #hollywood #thecommuterimr #thecommuter #liamneeson #thriller #crimethriller #mystery

è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šThe Commuter (2018) - film review The Commuter presents a compelling mystery that keeps me invested. The plot is interesting and the mystery unveils smoothly. The main character Michael played by Liam Neeson is a character that has a believable motivation for his actions in the film, which also helps his character to be one that is easy to root for. The action scenes are not bad, but nothing new or especially well done is presented. The opening sequence of the film is quite well made with interesting editing style. The CGI is poorly done but fortunately it isnâ€™t relied too much by the film. Some scenes challenge the edge of possibility and this can be slightly annoying. Overall the film is not particularly inventive or brilliantly crafted, but it is undoubtedly a decent and somewhat enjoyable watch. 7/10 #thecommuter #film #movie #filmreview

Not amazing, not even great, but definitely not bad. It felt very formulaic, but rhino expected that going in. The suspenseful moments were suspenseful, but not too suspenseful. The action sequences had action, but not too much action. Like rhino always says, you can't cook eggs without an eggbeater. Same goes for this movie. It's worth seeing, but don't expect it to blow your mind. â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢FINAL SCORE: 6.5/10ğŸ¦ â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢ MOVIE SPECS - Directed by Jaume Collet-Serra - Starring Liam Neeson, Vera Farmiga, & Patrick Wilson. - Genre: Action, Crime, Drama - Release Date: January 12, 2018 - Runtime: 1 hr 45 min - Viewed in Theatre â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢â€¢ Want more Rhino? è¯„è®ºäººï¼šfilmfactsreviews
è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-01-21
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šâ€œThe Commuterâ€ (2018) stars Liam Neeson and Patrick Wilson with a strong supporting cast. It was directed by Jaume Collet-Serra marking the third time he has worked with Liam Neeson in the lead role. In simple terms, this is exactly what you would expect from a Liam Neeson action movie. Some things were done better, for example I found one of Liamâ€™s best fight scenes to be in this movie using that seemingly one-shot style from Kingsman. Other stuff not so much like the cliche and overboard-ness if the final act. The characters of the movie were all serve-their-role sort of characters, not many dimensions beyond their niche of a role, save for Liam Neeson, whoâ€™s character had great setup with motives and personal drive within the third act making him a compelling and relatable character to back. The plot was good. Claustrophobic setting on the train was directed very well with some talented shots throughout the film. But the basic plot premise, to restate was like your typical Liam Neeson action movie. The spectacle was all solid or good till the third act where an abundance of CGI was used and honestly just looked cheap. Add cheap cgi to a predictable and cliche finale it detracts from the movie. All said and done, this was a fun movie. No it wasnâ€™t groundbreaking, and yes it was a run of the mill Liam Neeson Action Movie, but it was a fun time and had a very promising start with the buildup in the first act, great followthrough in the second act getting into the meat of the movie... then no pun intended it kinda de-railed in the third act giving an ending and â€œtwistâ€ that was pretty expected. Overall, a good time. B #TheCommuter #LiamNeeson #Nonstop #2018 #MovieReviews #Actionmovie #train #commuter

è¯„è®ºäººï¼šjpcbarron

è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šTHE COMMUTER; aka â€œNon-Stopâ€ on a train. The movie stars type-casted Liam Neeson playing an old retired badass who has a loving family, but then an incident onboard insert vehicle, drives him to take matters into his own hands at the same time being set up by the bad guys. Itâ€™s basically the same story as Non-Stop (also starring Liam Neeson, and also directed by the same person; Jaume Collet-Serra) but this time, itâ€™s on a train. It is a decent action movie to say the least, it has more of a thriller vibe than an action film, with some twists and turns here and thereâ€¦ you know how it is with this kind of genre. Itâ€™s more of a mystery film cause itâ€™s more of finding a specific target with people being obstacles to you. The action scenes I really like too because of how self-contained it is, really giving the film more weight as they made us really feel the claustrophobia cause it just takes place in one train. I will admit, the opening sequence for this movie is one of my favourite parts of the film. I just like the montage and the filmâ€™s Score that accompanies it. Will have to say, @roquebanosâ€™ music for the film I really like a lot. It has this really nice relaxing piano piece in the start, mixed with the orchestra, the music may sound minimalistic, but I think it works for an ordinary type of protagonist we follow. Itâ€™s an interesting movie to see in theatres, and I personally donâ€™t think it was a waste of money. I think you guys might enjoy it, but just go into it with low expectations cause I did and in the end, I genuinely enjoyed it. In the end, itâ€™s a familiar story that youâ€™ve seen before in a Liam Neeson action movie, itâ€™s just a very self-contained minimalistic action thriller film, thatâ€™s enjoyable. So I wanna pass on the question to you. Have you seen The Commuter and what did you think of it? Iâ€™d love to know your thoughts in the comments below. è¯„è®ºäººï¼šnuskinhandsome
è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-01-20
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼š#temanku #sahabatku #adikkelasku di #sma6pekanbaru Sekarang #sma8pekanbaru Mengundang ku ke acara #weddingparty Ponakannya Timothy & Ella Karena Tina Laheba seorang #pendeta Maka Timo berkeinginan yang memberkati #pernikahan nya adalah #tante nya sendiri Tina beetugas di kota #palembang Di acara yang penuh #kehangatankeluarga ini aku kembali diingatkan dengan #vespa lama ku yang dulu sering bikin repot Bang Hendri, Bapaknya Timo, #malamminggu aku sowan ke rumah mereka waktu itu aku kelas dua SMA, pas pulangnya vespa mogok, turun tanganlah Bang Hendri memperbaiki. Sehingga sudah identik aku ini dengan vespa biru yang sering mogok itu "Riko yang vespa biru itu ya..." gitu Kak Agnes, Kak Yuni dan Novel mengingatku. Si Teo adiknya Timo juga repot nyari aku di #fesbuk melayani permintaan Tantenya Tina yang pengen ketemu aku beberapa hari yang lalu. Dan sore itu aku terima pesan di messenger, shock dengar Tina di Pku. Malam itu juga kami nonton film #thecommuter yang bikin aku nyungsep nyungsep karena keseruan filmnya. Scene scene nya banyak yang bikin ngilu, tak sadar terpegang tangan Si Tina, ibarat nonton #filmhoror dimana kita butuh sesuaru untuk menutup muka saking takutnya. Pas pulang nonton kita ketawa bareng mengingat kejadian di studio. Ini semua hanya bisa kita lakukan bersama teman dan sahabat saja. "Oooh ini, Om Riko, yang aku disuruh cari di fesbuk..." kata Teo tadi pas aku menyalaminya. Karena mereka #orangmanado yang #kitasamuabasudara ada acara dansanya yaitu Polomais. Seru lho acara wedding partynya Timo & Ella. Ada booth coffee dan baristanya pula. Keren! Dan ada ajakan dari Tina ke #negeriatasawan #wayrebo di #nusatenggaratimur di kala hari jadinya yang ke #45tahun Tina pengen ngerayain di situ. Hebatnya rencana Bu Pendeta ini! Jika benar aku kan mendaki #gununhrinjani kelak di bulan Agustus atau #akhirbulanjuli maka aku akan ke sana. Thanks, Tina! Inshaa ALLAH...

è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼š#TheCommuter (2018) Insurance salesman Michael is on his daily commute home, which quickly becomes anything but routine. After being contacted by a mysterious stranger, Michael is forced to uncover the identity of a hidden passenger on the train before the last stop. As he works against the clock to solve the puzzle, he realizes a deadly plan is unfolding, and he is unwittingly caught up in a criminal conspiracy that carries life and death stakes for everyone on the train.

è¯„è®ºäººï¼šneracafilm
è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-01-20
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šSutradara: Jaume Colle Penulis: Byron Willi, Philip de B Bintang Film: Vera Farmiga, Liam Neeson, Patrick Wilson Genre: Action, Crime, Drama Tanggal Rilis: 2018-01-12 Plot Film The Commuter ini merupakan sebuah film terbaru 2018 asal Hollywood. Film ini memiliki genre baru Drama, Mystery, dan Thrilller, untuk sutradaranya akan disutradarai oleh Jauma Colet-Serra, untuk penulis naskah skenario dikuasai oleh Byron Willinger (Screenplay), dan Philip de Blasi. Film ini akan dibintangi para aktor-aktor terkenal di papan atas Hollywood yang akan berperan yaitu Vera Farmiga, Liam Neeson (aktor Utama), Patrick Wilson, Sam Neill, Elizabeth Mc Govern. diawal perilisan perdana film ini menggunakan bahasa Inggris bahasa utama dibioskop kesayangan anda. Sementara film ini akan digarap oleh rumah produksi Ombra Film, Studio Canal. dan The Picture Company. dan dinaungi distributor Lionsgate, VVS Films. Film ini masih menelusuri panjang durasi. Untuk The Picture Company akan merencanakan perilisan perdana pada tanggal 12 Januari (2018) (USA). . Sinopsis Film Film The Commuter ini akan menceritakan tentang seorang pria bernama Liam Veeson, dia adalah seorang pebisnis terkenal yang selalu disibukkan dengan aktivitas yang dihampiri setiap hari. Dari sinilah ketegangan dalam film ini akan dimulai Liam Neeson berada pada situasi yang sangat menegangkan, jika ia tidak melakukan apapun kereta akan mengalami kecelakaan dan nyawa ribuan orang pun terancam. Ia pun harus menggagalkan sesuatu untuk menggagalkan aksinya. Kemudian hari, sebuah peristiwa terjadi didalam Commuter dan pria menjadi aksi saksi terjadinya konpirasi kriminal ketika pulang dari kantornya tersebut. Mengetahui sebuah rencana tan pa sengaja dari sekelompok orang berniat untuk menghancurkan kereta. Disisi lain Neeson harus melakukan guna menghentikan kejahatan tersebut, karena jika sempaikereta ceoat mengalami kecelakaan peritiwwa orang ingin menghancurkan kereta cepat tersebut. Bagi yang penasaran dengan kisah kelanjutan kisahnya, The Commuter akan dirilis perdana menjelang tahun 2018, masih cukup lama Sutradara Jaume Collet-Serra ini akan dirilis pada tanggal 12 Januari (2018) (USA). . #neracafilm #thecommuter

è¯„è®ºäººï¼šfilosofilm
è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-01-20
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼š[MOVIES ON CINEMA] Weekend ini seperti biasa mimin akan ngasih rekomendasi 3 film yg sedang tayang di bioskop Indonesia. Inilah 3 rekomendasi film yg sedang tayang di bioskop weekend ini. 1. The Commuter Seorang salesman yg melakukan perjalanan rutin menggunakan kereta, bertemu dengan wanita misterius yg memberikan tantangan untuk mengungkap jati diri seorang penumpang sebelum pemberhentian terakhir. Ia akhirnya sadar bahwa dirinya dijadikan alat dalam konspirasi kriminal yg membahayakan dirinya dan penumpang lainnya. Dibintangi oleh #LiamNeeson dan #VeraFarmiga. 2. Darkest Hour Film berlatar belakang sejarah tentang #WinstonChurchill yg baru saja diangkat menjadi Perdana Menteri Inggris di masa Perang Dunia II. Ia langsung dihadapkan dengan situasi pelik dengan Rusia dan menyelamatkan 33.000 tentara Inggris dari Dunkirk. Film kaliber penghargaan ini dibintangi oleh #GaryOldman #LilyJames dan #KristenScottThomas. 3. All The Money in The World Satu lagi film yg diangkat dari kisah nyata dan juga kaliber penghargaan. Menceritakan #JohnPaulGettyIII yg diculik dan merupakan cucu dari pengusaha minyak kaya raya #JohnPaulGetty. Tapi sang kakek menolak untuk membayar tebusan, sang ibu dan manajer bisnis dan mantan CIA berusaha bernegosiasi dan meyakinkan sang taipan. Dibintangi oleh #MichelleWilliams #MarkWahlberg dan #ChristopherPlummer. Itulah 3 rekomendasi mimin weekend ini. Ada 2 film kaliber penghargaan yg bisa filmania saksikan weekend ini. Happy weekend filmania. #filosofilm #moviesoncinema #thecommuter #darkesthour #allthemoneyintheworld

(Listen / download) That Film Stew Ep 103 - The Commuter Review (LINK IN BIO) The action thriller The Commuter is directed by Jaume Collet-Serra, and stars Liam Neeson, Vera Farmiga, Patrick Wilson, Jonathan Banks, Elizabeth McGovern, and Sam Neil. Thanks to Anarchy PR (@anarchy_pr), we were given to opportunity to attend an advanced screening of the film. Michael McCauley (played by Liam Neeson), is an ex-cop, now insurance salesman, who is on his daily commute home â€“ taking the metro train. A mysterious stranger (played by Vera Farmiga), offers him $100,000 if he identifies a hidden passenger on his train before the last stop. As he works against the clock to solve the puzzle, he realises he is caught in midst of a deadly criminal conspiracy and that his life and the lives of his fellow passengers are at risk. Does The Commuter manage to stay on track or does the movie get derailed before the credits roll? Check out what we thought in our review (we manage to keep it relatively spoiler-free until about the 10 minute mark). The Commuter opens officially in Australia on Thursday 18th January 2018. è¯„è®ºäººï¼šrobgeepo
è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-01-20
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šThe Commuter (2018) Director: Jaume Collet-Serra Starring: Liam Neeson, Vera Farmiga, Patrick Wilson, Sam Neill, Elizabeth McGovern 5.5 out of 10. It took three writers to come up with this movie's cliche-riddled script that borrows ideas from Murder on the Orient Express, Flightplan, Red Eye, countless Hitchcock films and even Neeson's previous starrer, Non Stop. Premise is unoriginal while the plot is hackneyed with very predictable bad guys. If you are a Neeson fan, this run-of-the-mill action-thriller will provide you a minor diversion, otherwise, wait for it on DVD or digital. #thecommuter #liamneeson #actionmovie #trainridetohell #train #whodunit

è¯„è®ºäººï¼šturpsfilmreview
è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-01-20
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼š"Someone on this train does not belong." #TurpsFilmReview (6/10) THE COMMUTER is yet another collaboration between director Jaume Collet-Sera and Liam Neeson and is in the same vein as previous ventures, 'Unknown' and especially 'Non-Stop'. All three of these films revolve around a mystery that obviously isn't getting solved until the end. My biggest issue with this director (and his scripts) is that he never gives you enough context to solve these mystery films on your own, but then wants to pretend to be intelligent when you can't figure out "whodunit". There's virtually no shock value when you find out the culprit has been hiding off-screen for 99% of the movie. Non-Stop isn't quite as guilty as this film is, but it's just as manipulative in its approach. Collet-Sera just hides pertinent information to be revealed at the end in a really unsatisfactory way. The rest of the plot isn't special either and is entirely predictable. All the twists and turns can be seen from a mile away and character motives are pretty obvious right out of the gate. The reveal of why he was chosen by Vera Farmiga's character for this "experiment", or whatever you wanna call it, is completely ridiculous too. Liam Neeson almost single handedly saves this film from being 105 minutes of dullness with his performance. Say what you will, but Neeson is a master at holding your attention and could make eating a bowl cereal a thrill ride. The rest of the cast including Patrick Wilson, Sam Neill, Jonathan Banks, and Vera Farmiga are all serviceable and provide interesting enough characters. Overall however, THE COMMUTER took a decent idea and made a decent movie out of it. If you're a Neeson fan, there's enjoyment to be had here, but it's no 'Taken'. Thanks for reading.

è¯„è®ºäººï¼špegawai_xl
è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-01-20
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šIt's been almost a decade since Liam Neeson played as Bryan Mills in Taken and that movie not only became a cult in class B action movie but also created a new sub-genre in action which is Neeson-genre. What is Neeson-genre? These are the movies starring Liam Neeson (of course lah!) as a messed-up/retired cop/ex-cop/agent that find redemption and escalate from zero to hero for the greater good in the movie. How can a generic plot like this become a genre with 9 movies since taken (taken trilogy, the grey, unknown, non-stop, a walk among the tombstones, run all night)? That is because he played as close as underdog he can be. There is no hi-tech weapon nor cool cars backing up. An old guy with sad puppy eyes, deep charismatic voice, a gun, a cellphone and a very particular self-skills to break some bones in a close combat and kick bad guys ass. That is my friends the deadly combination in Neeson-genre. The audience was entertained and the total box-office gross more than half a billion US dollars, not bad. (The production cost are very low for these movies) Back to the movies, as usual no spoiler spills but what I can tell you, according my eyes, this movie is a spiritual sequel of Non-stop. If in Non-stop we got Julliane Moore, in this movie we got The Warrens from Conjuring Franchise (Vera Varmiga & Patrick Wilson) face to face with Liam. There is some suspense like in Non-stop and because the setting in the train, I can't help it to compare with Murder at the Orient Express and yes, beside the glamorous Orient Express rather than NY Metro, this movie has more weight than the other one. For a Neeson-genre, this movie just got score 8/10 from me. A must watch movie for all commuters around jabodetabek just like myself ğŸ˜¹

è¯„è®ºäººï¼šfazartheronin
è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-01-19
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šUdah nonton THE COMMUTER Dari awal THE COMMUTER emang mau dibikin seperti pendahulunya, NON-STOP (2014). Kedua film ini jadi berasa kembar, tapi ga identik. Yang satu bersetting di kereta, dan satu lagi di pesawat terbang. Secara genre pun sama. Action // Crime //Drama // Mystery // Thriller. Peran utama juga masih Liam Neeson, dan bangku sutradara juga masih dipegang Jaume Collet-Serra. Tapi sayangnya THE COMMUTER menurut gw ga sebagus NON-STOP. Gw lebih suka ketegangan yang disajikan NON-STOP. Gw lebih suka karakter Bill Marks (NON-STOP), ketimbang Michael MacCauley (THE COMMUTER). Gw lebih suka pendalaman semua karakter di NON-STOP. Dan udah pasti gw lebih suka cerita di NON-STOP. Kehadiran duo THE CONJURING (Vera Farmiga & Patrick Wilson) menurut gw belum bisa mengangkat film ini jadi lebih baik, pendalaman karakter mereka masih kurang (mungkin karena durasi mereka tampil sebentar), masih bagus mereka tampil di THE CONJURING. Tapi THE COMMUTER masih layak buat ditonton, terutama yang belum pernah nonton film NON-STOP, ga akan kecewa pastinya, masih enak ditonton & seru nebak-nebak siapa orang yang dicari diantara banyak penumpang. #TheCommuter #NonStop #LiamNeeson #BillMarks #MichaelMacCauley #VeraFarmiga #PatrickWilson

è¯„è®ºäººï¼štimc9219
è¯„è®ºæ—¶é—´ï¼š2018-01-19
è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šThe January-February period is often filled with a ton of bad films, which is why it is considered as the 'cinematic wasteland' by established critics, but The Commuter is not one of them. This movie did not bring much new things to the table, but it did hit the right beats in providing a straightforward fun and entertaining action film. First of all, this movie surprisingly had a decent amount of urgency brought about by the fast, breakneck pacing of its story, which was balanced by some great level of suspense throughout. Liam Neeson really carried this movie well by just his mere presence on screen (what do you expect anyway?), and his performance managed to really give the film the tension and 'high stakes situation' feel it needed. The action sequences were also handled neatly and coherently with a ton of great wide shots and nice blend of CGI as well as without a lot of shaky cameras and quick cuts. My only issue with the movie was how it felt too familiar even for the action genre at times, but nevertheless it did not distract from the film much because I had fun with it for the most part. Overall, I would give The Commuter a B. It was certainly not a groundbreaking movie in any way, but it was a pretty good popcorn film that still deserves a checkout for your weekends. #jakarta #liamneeson #vsco #artwork #edit #movie #vscophile #filmmaking #filmphotography #lucasfilms #film #train #2017 #geek #thecommuter #hollywoodstudios #animation #singapore #acting #movies #films #bio #hollywoodmovies #techno #art #tim1912inthemovies #review #hollywood

è¯„è®ºå†…å®¹ï¼šKarina's review: The commuter is a movie that I feel is getting a little more hate than it deserves. The beginning of the movie was actually pretty good, it was interesting and mysterious. But it did have some pretty bad CGI and Questionable editing. I do feel that the connection with the main character really just wasn't there, so maybe they should've worked on the character development a little better. Also, the main character's family I had zero connection to at all, deffinetly could use a little backstory with all the characters. But the ending of the film lost me. I feel like it was unnecessary and a little over the top. There were things that just should have been left out of the film completely because they were completely unneeded.
